The light green background represents time when property changes are forwarded
eConnection maintains list of bindings trough it. This enables controlled unbinding when connection
is broken, and automatic reconnect when connection comes back up.
ECMD_BIND commands are recorded, regardless if connection is up or down. If connection is down
when ECMD_BIND is received, the connection sends ECMD_SRV_UNBIND reply back to client binding.
ECMD_BIND_REPLY commands are recorded only when connection is up. When connection is down,
the connection replies with immediate ECMD_UNBIND to server binding.

If there is binding is disconnected, foward calls are ignored.
If flow control is disabled, then do not wait for ack.
If this is binding within same thread, disable flow control and do not send ECMD_ACKs at all.
